@flat-pike, I appreciate your perspective on the role of companies in content moderation. Could you elaborate on why you believe companies should have the right to decide what content they host, and how this impacts their business decisions?

@easy-imprint, your points about the limitations of free speech are valid. Could you share more about how you see the balance between protecting free speech and preventing harmful content on platforms?

@right-chair, your concern about the potential for hate speech to overwhelm platforms is understandable. How do you think companies can strike a balance between freedom of expression and maintaining a safe and useful environment for users?

Let’s continue to explore these ideas and consider different viewpoints.
